## 4. Risk Assessment (High-Care Areas — This Project)
- **Animation magic & "pretty" bar**: The letterIn cascade + pointer holo shine are the soul. New open transition must not feel janky, must not fight the existing letter-block anim or 3d rotate. Mitigation: build on existing @keyframes (letterIn, holoShine), add 1-2 new tasteful ones (unfold, wideOpen). Use transform + opacity only. Test mentally on mount + toggle. Keep RAF/shimmer auto only when open or always subtle.
- **Closed state design**: Must still feel "Hadacard" and holo (not a dumb box). Use same .holo-card shell + a front face with the handwritten name large, tiny "tap to open" or wax-seal hint using existing svgs or minimal emoji/text. Profile pic can be smaller or peek. Holo layers stay (delight even when "sealed").
- **Wide open**: "Wide" = generous horizontal breathing + message as hero (current message is already large italic). When open, relax inner padding or use a class that allows the card to feel more landscape/letter-sheet (via wrapper aspect or max-w in parent, but since component owns inner, use flex-col to a more expansive body area + slightly adjusted --card-aspect or override in open). Keep aspect-ratio base for 3d consistency; "wide" via layout + font scaling inside.
- **Controlled vs uncontrolled**: Support both (prop `open` + optional `onOpenChange`). Internal createSignal for default. Toggle on card click when closed (haptic 'medium' or 'success'). When controlled, respect prop (no internal flip unless callback).
- **Zero break on existing**: All current usage (home with config.* + client:load) must render identically when open (default). No new required props.
- **Types move**: Adding to @/types is low risk (already the home of CardMeta). Update re-exports if needed. Component import change only.
- **Perf / mobile**: New anims are CSS + tiny signals. No extra RAF beyond existing shimmer. Touch: the whole card remains the hit target for open when closed; when open the pointer 3d continues.
- **IIPS / duplication**: Do not leave old interfaces behind in component. Remove completely. Extract util is pure (no side effects).
- **"Before the orchid"**: The open mode + letter aesthetic directly sets emotional stage (personal message first, then the living 3d bloom as the "gift inside the letter"). No change to OrchidViewer or its page needed here.
- Low risk overall: additive feature inside existing component + pure extract + type move. Build catches import/alias instantly.

## 5. Invariant Check — IIPS + Love Letter + $
- **IIPS**: Code will read like a careful handwritten letter — precise, sparkling, never sloppy. Small pure fns at top. Getters for props. Comments that explain "why the open feels like unfolding a real letter". No random strings, elegant defaults.
- **$ (in-project source module kind)**: New util at src/utils/letters.ts (typed name "letters" for the split + any future letter/anim helpers). Types live only in src/types/. Component stays presentation. No new concepts outside existing solid/astro patterns.
- **Preserve magic**: Holo foil/glitter/shine/glare + pointer vars + autoShimmer untouched in spirit (enhanced for open state perhaps). letter-block cascade kept + reusable. haptics on open gesture. glass/gradient/pastel/pink-gold palette. "— with love, always". Profile + cap + candles stay. Audio boundaries untouched (none in this component).
- **Emotional tone**: The open animation must feel intimate, surprising, joyful — like she is the one carefully opening a physical letter from you. Wide pretty message area = the heart of it.
- Does not touch: particles (Frutiger), audio (any), three (Orchid), tomls, global nav, home scripts.

## 6. Alternatives Considered
- Keep types local in component: violates explicit "port all types into src/types".
- Inline the split fn or duplicate: violates "generalizable src/utils".
- Pure prop-less always-open + separate "OpenCard" component: over-fragment; job asks for *a mode* on the hadacard.
- Heavy JS-driven open (multiple RAF for flap): unnecessary; CSS + a couple staged signals (profileVisible, titlesVisible, bodyVisible) + transition classes is IIPS + cheap + smooth.
- Change aspect-ratio on open (breaks 3d perspective consistency): avoid; achieve "wide" via inner content breathing + optional outer class passthrough.
- Make open the only mode or default false: would break home instantly; default true + explicit closed for special uses (e.g. gift "unopened" presentation).
- Edit global.css heavily: prefer minimal or none; if layers need a .holo-card.open variant we can add 1-2 rules, but try first with existing + inline style overrides + component <style> for any new keyframes if they feel component-private.

Chosen path: controlled+uncontrolled open, closed front reuses holo shell + minimal new content, CSS transitions + existing letterIn for most reveals, one new util file + one types addition, component does the heavy lifting. Perfect scope.

